law.text:
For a period of six (6) months following June 16, 1972, an applicant for a license shall be issued a license without examination provided applicant:
Has been principally engaged as a hearing aid dealer or fitter for a total period of at least two (2) continuous years within a period of three (3) years immediately prior to June 16, 1972;
Is a person of good moral character;
Is eighteen (18) years of age or older; and
Is free of contagious or infectious disease.
